TITLE: Serialize and Deserialize Rust Struct to JSON using Serde
DESCRIPTION: This Rust example demonstrates how to define a struct, derive `Serialize` and `Deserialize` traits, and then use `serde_json` to convert an instance of the struct into a JSON string and back. It showcases basic JSON serialization and deserialization, printing the results to the console.

SOURCE: https://github.com/serde-rs/serde/blob/master/serde/README.md#_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: rust
CODE:
```
use serde::{Deserialize, Serialize};

#[derive(Serialize, Deserialize, Debug)]
struct Point {
    x: i32,
    y: i32,
}

fn main() {
    let point = Point { x: 1, y: 2 };

    // Convert the Point to a JSON string.
    let serialized = serde_json::to_string(&point).unwrap();

    // Prints serialized = {"x":1,"y":2}
    println!("serialized = {}", serialized);

    // Convert the JSON string back to a Point.
    let deserialized: Point = serde_json::from_str(&serialized).unwrap();

    // Prints deserialized = Point { x: 1, y: 2 }
    println!("deserialized = {:?}", deserialized);
}
```

