TITLE: Configure Serde and serde_json dependencies in Cargo.toml
DESCRIPTION: This TOML configuration snippet defines the required dependencies for a Rust project using Serde. It includes `serde` with the `derive` feature enabled for automatic trait implementation and `serde_json` for JSON serialization and deserialization capabilities.

SOURCE: https://github.com/serde-rs/serde/blob/master/README.md#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: toml
CODE:
```
[dependencies]

# The core APIs, including the Serialize and Deserialize traits. Always
# required when using Serde. The "derive" feature is only required when
# using #[derive(Serialize, Deserialize)] to make Serde work with structs
# and enums defined in your crate.
serde = { version = "1.0", features = ["derive"] }

# Each data format lives in its own crate; the sample code below uses JSON
# but you may be using a different one.
serde_json = "1.0"
```

