TITLE: Tokio I/O Driver Readiness Event Handling Logic
DESCRIPTION: Explains the logic for clearing readiness events in Tokio's I/O driver. Readiness is only cleared if the current driver tick matches the tick associated with the `ReadyEvent`, preventing issues when events are processed after the tick has advanced.

SOURCE: https://github.com/tokio-rs/tokio/blob/master/tokio/docs/reactor-refactor.md#_snippet_8

LANGUAGE: APIDOC
CODE:
```
Readiness Clearing Logic:
  - The `readiness()` function returns a `ReadyEvent` containing the resource's readiness value and the current driver tick.
  - When `clear_readiness()` is called with a `ReadyEvent`:
    - Readiness is only cleared if the current driver tick matches the `tick` component within the provided `ReadyEvent`.
    - If ticks do not match, the call to `readiness()` in the next iteration will not block, and the new tick will be included in the `ReadyToken`.
```

